# Feed Design System: Compact Government-Style Minimalism

Apply this design aesthetic to all UI components unless explicitly overridden. The feed pages use a hyper-compact, flat design inspired by minimalist government websitesâ€”prioritizing information density and functional clarity over visual flourish.

## Design Rules

**Spacing**: Use `gap-2` (8px) or `gap-3` (12px) for element spacing, `p-[10px]` for card padding, `space-y-3` (12px) for vertical stacks. Never exceed these values unless necessary for touch targets.

**Typography**: Primary text uses `text-xs` (12px), headings use `text-sm` (14px) with `font-semibold` or `font-medium`. Avoid larger sizes except for page titles or critical CTAs.

**Borders & Backgrounds**: Cards use `border border-gray-200` with `rounded-md` (6px), white backgrounds (`bg-white`), subtle hover states (`hover:bg-gray-50`). No shadows, gradients, or depth effects.

**Icons**: Size `w-3 h-3` (12px) or `w-4 h-4` (16px) maximum, `text-gray-500` transitioning to `text-gray-700` on hover. Icon-to-text spacing: `gap-1.5` or `gap-2`.

**Vertical Rhythm**: `space-y-0.5` (2px) for tightly related elements, `space-y-1.5` (6px) for grouped items, `space-y-3` (12px) for card sections.

**Colors**: Limit to `gray-50`, `gray-100`, `gray-200`, `gray-500`, `gray-600`, `gray-700`, `gray-900`. Body text: `text-gray-600`, headings: `text-gray-900`, metadata: `text-gray-500`.

**Interactions**: Subtle hover effects (`hover:bg-gray-50`, `hover:text-gray-900`) with `transition-colors`. No transforms, scale effects, or animations beyond color changes.
